This paper discusses the intersection of machine learning and human-computer interaction, specifically in the context of explainable AI. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also deals with text classification, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper evaluates the quality of explanations, which is related to the field of machine learning evaluation, falling under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
